title: Anger in Italy as tourist filmed carving names into the Colosseum
description: Italy's culture minister says a tourist who was filmed carving his and his girlfriend's names into the Colosseum in Rome should be "identified and sanctioned".

title: 'Any blackmail is doomed to failure,' defiant Putin warns after attempted rebellion
description: Vladimir Putin has warned "any blackmail is doomed for failure" - days after an attempted rebellion led by Wagner boss Yevgeny Prigozhin.

title: Russian fighter jets scrambled after two UK warplanes detected near border, Moscow claims
description: Russian fighter jets were scrambled after at least two UK warplanes were detected near the country's border, Moscow has claimed.

title: Liz Truss calls for UK to have plan if Russia collapses
description: Former prime minister Liz Truss has called on the government to have a plan in place in case the Russian government under Vladimir Putin collapses.

title: Exiled Wagner boss breaks silence in new audio message
description: Exiled Wagner boss Yevgeny Prigozhin has released an audio message for the first time since abandoning a march to Moscow.

title: Speculation rife about Shoigu and Prigozhin's whereabouts in absence of any clear direction from Putin
description: The dust is settling. The damage is deep. And the question remains, especially in the absence of any clear direction from Vladimir Putin - what happens next?

title: 14-year-old boy dies during hike in 48C heat - as stepdad loses life trying to get help
description: A 14-year-old boy and his stepfather have died in Texas after they went on a hike in extreme heat where temperatures reached 48.3C (119F).

title: Russian squatter leaves axed embassy site after high court loss
description: Australia's high court has dismissed Russia's bid to challenge laws preventing it from building a new embassy on land near the country's parliament in Canberra.

title: Russian defence minister spotted for first time since attempted Wagner coup
description: Russia's defence minister was spotted in his first public appearance since Wagner boss Yevgeny Prigozhin stood down his group of rebel mercenaries.
